<div id="Idea_3993"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3993-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3993">Create an Ombudsman for the US Government&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/8817-4049">bj</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">2 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Create an Ombudsman, an organization responsible to ensure that problems dealing with the US Government are properly handled.<br/><br/>Individual departments and agencies would still be responsible for handling problems, but the central Ombudsman would 1) be a place to go for individuals who don't know how to find the correct location, 2) track and followup to ensure all requests are handled in a timely manner, 3) monitor agency and department Ombudsman organizations to watch for areas that aren't handled well.<br/><br/>Many requests would be answered "it's the law, ask you legislators (here is there contact information)" or "it's federal regulation (the department responsible for updating the regulations is ...)", but answering other requests can really help people who are frustrated about bad treatment.<br/></div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3993" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3993', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2255&topicID=3993')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3993"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2255">Uncategorized</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3993"></div>
</div></td>
