<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3983"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3983-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3983">Charge Oil and Utility Company execs that buy green patents in order to stop them from being produced with crimes against humani&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/5646-4049">luvwith</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">2 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Charge decision makers at any polluting business who buys a patent for a cleaner technology - simply to make sure it never comes to market - with treason or crimes against humanity. <br/><br/>At the very least it should be illegal to buy a patent for the purposes of keeping it from being produced and given the amount of money at stake penalties must be severe. A one percent increase in an engines efficiency means trillions in lost profits for big oil.<br/><br/>Air and water pollution causes hundreds of thousands, if not millions, of deaths every year and is putting the continued existence of human life on this planet at risk so that a very few can make obscene profits while the vast majority needlessly suffer respiratory illness, cancer, global warming, etc.<br/><br/>It is standard for Oil companies to buy up battery and other fuel efficiency technology in order to keep it off the market or "develop it so slowly that it grinds progress to a halt. And of course that puts the best, most efficient, least toxic materials off limits for anyone else trying to develop similar technology…seriously hampering advancement of cleaner engines.<br/><br/>The Oil and Utility companies get the patents by instigating frivolous lawsuits they know they'll never win but that the smaller companies can't afford to litigate. They file bogus claim after bogus claim with an infinite supply of legal talent on permanent salary and unlimited funds. <br/><br/>First they will bankrupt a company…then they offer the environmental entrepreneur a chunk money to wash their hands of the project and sell the patent once there is no chance the company can ever recover financially or afford to produce it once they've hemorrhaged all their capital in legal fees. <br/><br/>Then they force a draconian non-disclosure agreement and the public never hears about it. They spend billions of dollars in TV and radio ads to green up their images and to make sure no one ever does a story on the practice.<br/><br/>If that is not a crime against humanity what is?<br/></div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3983" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3983', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2255&topicID=3983')">Comments (3)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3983"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2255">Uncategorized</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=oil">oil</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=pollution">pollution</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=patents">patents</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=green">green</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=renewable energy">renewable energy</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3983"></div>
