<a href="/akira/dtd/3980-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3980">Designate the Republican National Committee as a terrorist organization&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/5044-4049">gary</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">2 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Under rules instituted during the Bush administration, the Executive Branch at its sole discretion can declare an organization to be terrorist, making it illegal to supply funds or other resources to said organization.<br/><br/>One of the worst terrorist attacks in recent memory has been the invasion and occupation of Iraq, which led to the deaths of millions of Iraqis. This occupation was conceived, planned, and executed by agents of the Republican Party. Said party has also directed billions of dollars of US public money towards the support of terrorist attacks by the Israeli government against the people of Gaza and against its neighbors.<br/><br/>The RNC has far more blood on its hands than Hamas or any of the other groups the Bush administration declared to be illegal. Not only does the RNC support blatant and bloody terrorism, they've used trillions of our tax dollars to do it and wrecked our economy in the process. Let's apply their own rules to help bring them to justice.</div>
